description._content: Description: A Gilbertese dressed, for ceremonial purposes, in the fibrous envelope which binds the base of the coconut frond to the tree. Location: Kiribati ------------------------------------------------------ Description: The old men of Ocean Island chosen as delegates on the Native Lands' Commission, 1932. Location: Ocean Island, Kiribati Date: 1932 ------------------------------------------------------ Our Catalogue Reference: Part of CO 1069/642. This image is part of the Colonial Office photographic collection held at The National Archives. Feel free to share it within the spirit of the Commons. Please use the comments section below the pictures to share any information you have about the people, places or events shown. We have attempted to provide place information for the images automatically but our software may not have found the correct location.
